---- MODULE MCDieHarder ----

(**************************************************************************)
(* The following definitions duplicate the original Die Hard problem.   *)
(**************************************************************************)

CONSTANTS   Goal,   \* The goal value.
            Jug,    \* The capacity of the jug.
            Capacity, \* The capacity of the container.
            Empty,  \* The empty set.
            Full,   \* The set containing the value 1.
            Water   \* The set containing the value 0.

VARIABLES   m,      \* The current state of the machine.
            n,      \* The number of moves made so far.
            s       \* The current state of the container.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
MCJug ==    \* Define a function to compute the capacity of the jug.
    [j \in 1..10] : j

MCCapacity ==    \* Define a function to compute the capacity of the container.
    [c \in 1..10] : c

Spec == \* The specification.
    /\ m = 0
    /\ n = 0
    /\ s = Empty
    /\ (m = 1 /\ s = Full)
    /\ (m = 2 /\ s = Water)
